v1.commit_message:
Few improvements for WaitGroup and OneShotEvent: (#235)

Few improvements for WaitGroup and OneShotEvent:
1. Relax memory orders for OneShotEvent
2. OneShotEvent::Await was incorrect named, in reality it was AwaitSticky
3. Implement real OneShotEvent::Await
4. Add OneShotEvent::Call, same as Set, but doesn't prevent adding new jobs.
It's useful for scenarios like:
one thread do some jobs some time, for an example Writer::Commit.
other thread, for an example in Transaction::Commit, want to wait and when first Writer::Commit is called.

2. OneShotEvent::Await was incorrect named, in reality it was AwaitSticky
3. Implement real OneShotEvent::Await
4. Add OneShotEvent::Call, same as Set, but doesn't prevent adding new jobs.
It's useful for scenarios like:
one thread do some jobs some time, for an example Writer::Commit.
other thread, for an example in Transaction::Commit, want to wait and when first Writer::Commit is called.
